## 10. ASCII SEQUENCE DIAGRAM: Typical Switch Sequence

```
PHASE 1: Drain & Setup
========================

[Main simulation running: AtomicSimple]
  | curTick() = 1000000, insts = 5000000
  |
  | Exit event fires: "a thread reached max insts"
  |
  | m5.switchCpus(system, [(AtomicSimple, Timing)])
  |   |
  |   +-- m5.drain()
  |   |     +-- DrainManager.tryDrain()
  |   |     |     ... iterate simulate() until all Drained ...
  |   |     +-- DrainManager.isDrained() returns True
  |   |
  |   +-- old_cpu.switchOut()  [AtomicSimple]
  |   |     +-- _switchedOut = True
  |   |     +-- flushTLBs()
  |   |     |     +-- for each thread: tc.getMMUPtr()->flushAll()
  |   |     +-- powerState = OFF
  |   |
  |   +-- system.setMemoryMode(timing)  [if needed]
  |   |     +-- Invalidate caches if going to atomic_noncaching
  |   |
  |   +-- new_cpu.takeOverFrom(old_cpu)  [Timing]
  |         +-- for each thread i:
  |         |     +-- newTC = threadContexts[i]
  |         |     +-- oldTC = old_cpu->threadContexts[i]
  |         |     +-- newTC->getIsaPtr()->setThreadContext(newTC)
  |         |     +-- newTC->takeOverFrom(oldTC)
  |         |     |     +-- copyArchRegs()  [regs, PC, status]
  |         |     |     +-- setContextId(), setThreadId()
  |         |     |     +-- oldTC->setStatus(Halted)
  |         |     +-- system->replaceThreadContext(newTC)
  |         |     +-- newTC->getMMUPtr()->takeOverFrom(oldTC->getMMUPtr())
  |         |
  |         +-- interrupts = old_cpu->interrupts
  |         |     +-- for each tid: interrupts[tid]->setThreadContext(newTC)
  |         |     +-- old_cpu->interrupts.clear()
  |         |
  |         +-- getInstPort().takeOverFrom(&old_cpu->getInstPort())
  |         |     +-- L1 I$ now connected to Timing CPU
  |         +-- getDataPort().takeOverFrom(&old_cpu->getDataPort())
  |         |     +-- L1 D$ now connected to Timing CPU
  |         +-- modelResetPort.takeOverFrom(...)
  |         +-- _switchedOut = False
  |         +-- _pid, _taskId = old_cpu->_pid, _taskId
  |         +-- powerState = oldCPU->powerState (e.g., ON)
  |

PHASE 2: Resume & Simulate
============================

  | DrainManager.resume()
  |   +-- for each object: drainResume()
  |   +-- DrainState transitions: Resuming -> Running
  |
  | Simulation continues with Timing CPU
  |   +-- curTick() = 1000000  [preserved]
  |   +-- PC, regs, memory [from AtomicSimple] [preserved]
  |   +-- L1 caches [unchanged]
  |   +-- TLBs [empty, flushed]
  |
  v [Timing continues simulating from here]

PHASE 3: Old CPU State
=======================

  [AtomicSimple remains in memory]
    +-- _switchedOut = True
    +-- powerState = OFF
    +-- threadContexts[*].status = Halted
    +-- Can be switched back by new switch: (Timing, AtomicSimple)
    +-- Or deleted when simulation ends
```

